name: CompositeMessageLookup
comment: This is a message lookup mechanism that delegates to one of a collection of individual intl/message_lookup_by_library.MessageLookupByLibrary instances.

availableMessages.name: availableMessages
availableMessages.comment: A map from locale names to the corresponding lookups.

localeExists.name: localeExists
localeExists.comment: Return true if we have a message lookup for intl/message_lookup_by_library.CompositeMessageLookup.localeExists.localeName.

lookupMessage.name: lookupMessage
lookupMessage.comment: Look up the message with the given intl/message_lookup_by_library.CompositeMessageLookup.lookupMessage.name and intl/message_lookup_by_library.CompositeMessageLookup.lookupMessage.locale and return the translated version with the values in intl/message_lookup_by_library.CompositeMessageLookup.lookupMessage.args interpolated. If nothing is found, return intl/message_lookup_by_library.CompositeMessageLookup.lookupMessage.message_str. The intl/message_lookup_by_library.CompositeMessageLookup.lookupMessage.desc and intl/message_lookup_by_library.CompositeMessageLookup.lookupMessage.examples parameters are ignored

addLocale.name: addLocale
addLocale.comment: If we do not already have a locale for intl/message_lookup_by_library.CompositeMessageLookup.addLocale.localeName then intl/message_lookup_by_library.CompositeMessageLookup.addLocale.findLocale will be called and the result stored as the lookup mechanism for that locale.

hashCode.name: hashCode
hashCode.comment:
Get a hash code for this object.

All objects have hash codes. Hash codes are guaranteed to be the same for objects that are equal when compared using the equality operator ==. Other than that there are no guarantees about the hash codes. They will not be consistent between runs and there are no distribution guarantees.

If a subclass overrides intl/message_lookup_by_library.CompositeMessageLookup.hashCode it should override the equality operator as well to maintain consistency.

runtimeType.name: runtimeType
runtimeType.comment: A representation of the runtime type of the object.

==.comment:
The equality operator.

The default behavior for all dart-core.Objects is to return true if and only if this and intl/message_lookup_by_library.CompositeMessageLookup.==.other are the same object.

Override this method to specify a different equality relation on a class. The overriding method must still be an equivalence relation. That is, it must be:

  • Total: It must return a boolean for all arguments. It should never throw or return null.

  • Reflexive: For all objects o, o == o must be true.

  • Symmetric: For all objects o1 and o2, o1 == o2 and o2 == o1 must either both be true, or both be false.

  • Transitive: For all objects o1, o2, and o3, if o1 == o2 and o2 == o3 are true, then o1 == o3 must be true.

The method should also be consistent over time, so equality of two objects should not change over time, or at least only change if one of the objects was modified.

If a subclass overrides the equality operator it should override the intl/message_lookup_by_library.CompositeMessageLookup.hashCode method as well to maintain consistency.

toString.name: toString
toString.comment: Returns a string representation of this object.

noSuchMethod.name: noSuchMethod
noSuchMethod.comment:
intl/message_lookup_by_library.CompositeMessageLookup.noSuchMethod is invoked when users invoke a non-existent method on an object. The name of the method and the arguments of the invocation are passed to intl/message_lookup_by_library.CompositeMessageLookup.noSuchMethod in an dart-core.Invocation. If intl/message_lookup_by_library.CompositeMessageLookup.noSuchMethod returns a value, that value becomes the result of the original invocation.

The default behavior of intl/message_lookup_by_library.CompositeMessageLookup.noSuchMethod is to throw a dart-core.NoSuchMethodError.
